Sentencas: Oxide scale formations in anode gas atmospheres were investigated for three different Fe-Cr alloys as interconnects in solid oxide fuel cells (ZMG232, SUS430, and Fe-Cr-W).
Titulo: Application of Fe-Cr alloys to solid oxide fuel cells for cost-reduction - Oxidation behavior of alloys in methane fuel

Sentencas: Oxidation with anode gases (CH4, H2O, CO, and CO2) caused a relatively thick oxide scale formation on the alloy surfaces even in low oxygen partial pressures at 1073 K.
Titulo: Application of Fe-Cr alloys to solid oxide fuel cells for cost-reduction - Oxidation behavior of alloys in methane fuel

Sentencas: The distribution of elements in the oxide scale and the growth rates of oxide scales were compared among the examined alloys by glow discharge optical emission spectrometry (GDOES).
Titulo: Application of Fe-Cr alloys to solid oxide fuel cells for cost-reduction - Oxidation behavior of alloys in methane fuel

Sentencas: Mn-Fe-Cr spinels and Cr2O3 were formed on ZMG232 and SUS430 surfaces, whereas only Cr2O3 formation was observed on Fe-Cr-W surface.
Titulo: Application of Fe-Cr alloys to solid oxide fuel cells for cost-reduction - Oxidation behavior of alloys in methane fuel

Sentencas: Oxide scale thickness grew with annealing time by a parabolic relationship, and the growth rates were in the orders of 10(-6) to 10(-5)mum(2)
Titulo: Application of Fe-Cr alloys to solid oxide fuel cells for cost-reduction - Oxidation behavior of alloys in methane fuel

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity after forming oxide scales was different depending on the oxide scale phases and thickness.
Titulo: Application of Fe-Cr alloys to solid oxide fuel cells for cost-reduction - Oxidation behavior of alloys in methane fuel

Sentencas: The conductivity was in the order of 10S cm(-2) at 973 K for ZMG232 alloy.
